# PINFO-194 — explicit Trivy CVE allowlist.
#
# Each entry must carry a CVE ID, the affected component, and a brief
# justification. Re-evaluate every CVE listed here at least once per
# quarter: an entry that has been here for more than 3 months without
# being re-checked is a smell.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Blank lines and lines starting with #
# are ignored. Trivy applies this list AFTER its severity filter, so
# only HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs we explicitly accept end up here.

# nghttp2-libs CVE-2026-27135 — HTTP/2 DoS via malformed frames.
# Affects nghttp2-libs 1.68.0-r0 in our pinned nginx-unprivileged
# digest (PINFO-196). Fix is in 1.68.1 upstream but the alpine
# rebuild of nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:stable-alpine has not been
# published yet. Risk for us is bounded:
#   - nginx in our frontend pod only serves static SPA assets — no
#     /api proxy via nginx, that goes through Kong;
#   - the only HTTP/2 exposure we have terminates on Cloudflare's
#     edge, not on this nginx (cloudflared opens a plain HTTP tunnel
#     to the in-cluster ingress).
# To re-check: run `docker buildx imagetools inspect
# nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:stable-alpine` periodically and bump
# the digest in k8s/frontend/frontend-deployment.yaml +
# frontend/Dockerfile when the new alpine image carries 1.68.1+.
CVE-2026-27135
